Description: Papyrus (three fragments). Demotic account or school exercise on the recto; versos blank. Palimpsest. Two columns of numbers. Fragment A: column 1 traces; column 2, three lines. Fragment B: traces. Fragment C: column 1, eight lines; column 2, 11 lines. Fragments are torn on both sides and top and bottom.
Curator's comments: The text consists of two columns of numbers, most of which begin with 40 and then a single digit.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380967) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380967)
